  "prompt": "Which US Senate seats are up for reelection in 2018?",
  "response": "In the 2018 U.S. Senate elections, the following seats were up for reelection:\n\n1. Alaska - Dan Sullivan (R)\n2. Arizona - Jeff Flake (R) - Not seeking re-election\n3. California - Dianne Feinstein (D)\n4. Colorado - Cory Gardner (R)\n5. Connecticut - Chris Murphy (D)\n6. Delaware - Tom Carper (D)\n7. Florida - Bill Nelson (D)\n8. Hawaii - Mazie Hirono (D)\n9. Indiana - Joe Donnelly (D)\n10. Iowa - Chuck Grassley (R)\n11. Maine - Angus King (I) (running for a full term)\n12. Maryland - Ben Cardin (D)\n13. Massachusetts - Elizabeth Warren (D)\n14. Michigan - Debbie Stabenow (D)\n15. Minnesota - Amy Klobuchar (D)\n16. Mississippi - Thad Cochran (R) - Resigned, appointed Cindy Hyde-Smith (R) for the remainder of the term\n17. Missouri - Claire McCaskill (D)\n18. Nevada - Dean Heller (R)\n19. New Jersey - Bob Menendez (D)\n20. New Mexico - Martin Heinrich (D)\n21. New York - Kirsten Gillibrand (D)\n22. North Dakota - Heidi Heitkamp (D)\n23. Ohio - Sherrod Brown (D)\n24. Pennsylvania - Bob Casey Jr. (D)\n25. Rhode Island - Sheldon Whitehouse (D)\n26. Tennessee - Bob Corker (R) - Not seeking re-election\n27. Texas - Ted Cruz (R)\n28. Utah - Orrin Hatch (R) - Not seeking re-election\n29. Vermont - Bernie Sanders (I)\n30. Virginia - Tim Kaine (D)\n31. Washington - Maria Cantwell (D)\n32. West Virginia - Joe Manchin (D)\n33. Wisconsin - Tammy Baldwin (D)\n\nThese elections were part of a midterm election cycle where 35 Senate seats were contested.",
